title: Cruise Death Victim Identified As Sydney Woman, Suzanne Rees | 10 News
description: The 80-year-old cruise passenger who died after she was left behind on a Queensland island has been identified as Sydney woman Suzanne Rees. In a statement to 10 News, Suzanne's daughter, Katherine, said there was a failure of care and common sense. title: Trio Who Assaulted Ex-Cricketer Stuart MacGill Avoids Jail | 10 News
description: Three men who took Stuart MacGill to an isolated, abandoned shed and assaulted him have today walked out of court, avoiding further jail time. The court heard the former Australian cricketer was targeted over a drug rip-off involving another person, and they were after him for cash. title: $7.9 Billion Medicare Bulk Billing Overhaul To Take Effect In November | 10 News+
description: Australians will enjoy cheaper visits to the doctor starting November 1, when a multibillion-dollar overhaul of the Medicare bulk billing system comes into effect. GP clinics will be offered more financial incentives if they provide free appointments to any Medicare card holder. For women, the federal government scheme also includes larger rebates for menopause health assessments and long-term contraceptives. title: Trump-Xi Meeting Revolves Around Tariffs, Rare Earth Minerals & Fentanyl | 10 News+
description: US President Donald Trump and Chinese President Xi Jinping have met for the first time in six years, on the sidelines of the APEC Summit in South Korea. The highly anticipated meeting revolved around the drawn-out trade war between the world’s two superpowers. Trump called his Chinese counterpart a “tough negotiator”, and Xi said it is normal for their two countries “to have friction”. title: Meet The Australian Attorney Writing Laws For Outer Space | 10 News+
description: Steven Freeland is an Australian attorney with the astronomical assignment of writing guidelines for outer space. There are now 90 space-faring nations battling it out in the cosmos, along with 14,000 live satellites and millions of space debris. Freeland chairs a United Nations committee of 110 member states, which has until 2027 to reach a unanimous agreement on interstellar laws.
